b'2020 is looking like more of the same, according to #JPMorgan Global Research. Here\xe2\x80\x99s why :chart_increasing::
\xe2\xa0\x80
:keycap_1: Institutional investors are increasing their positions in equity futures, which may point to a reduction in value. However, a major reversal is unlikely and would require a significant trigger.
\xe2\xa0\x80
:keycap_2: The Great Rotation seems unlikely to happen in the near future. Recent fund flows show that rebalancing is a higher priority over long-term momentum.
\xe2\xa0\x80
:keycap_3: Forecasts for yield increases may be misleading. For the past ~20 years, economic forecasters predicted rising yields, but have seen the opposite each time.'
